translated: Fransson, Gustav Einar Albin, head teacher, Varberg, born on August 26, 1890 in Väckelsång, Kronoberg. Married once to Edith Johansson in 1923. They had a daughter named Brita, born in 1932. Gustav passed his teacher's exam in Växjö in 1917. He traveled to Germany, Austria and Switzerland in 1921 with a stipend to study. He was a substitute teacher in Södertälje in 1917 and in Katrineholm in 1918 before becoming a regular teacher there from 1918-1922. In 1923, he became the head teacher of Varberg's primary school. He was a member of the board of Sweden's head teacher association since 1938 and vice chairman since 1946. He was a member of the city council since 1930, vice chairman since 1947, member of the preparedness committee since 1940 and member of the board of the Varberg district of the Swedish Red Cross since 1926. He was a member of the Varberg Animal Welfare Society since 1933, serving as chairman from 1933-1941, and a member of the board of the Nordic Local Chapter since 1941. He was a member of the Odd Fellows, serving as headmaster from 1937-1938.
